I believe that I have found a trigonometric expression for both the ceiling and floor function, and I seek confirmation that it is, indeed, correct. Update. $$\begin{align}
\lfloor x \rfloor &= x - \frac12+f(x) \\[4pt] 
\lceil  x \rceil  &= x + \frac12+g(x)
\end{align}$$ where $$\begin{align}
f(x) &= \begin{cases}
\frac12, & x\in\Bbb{Z} \\[4pt]
0, &x=\frac12n, n\in\Bbb{Z} \\[4pt]
\frac1\pi \tan^{-1}(\cot(\pi x)), &\text{otherwise}
\end{cases} \\[10pt]
g(x) &= \begin{cases}
-\frac12, & x\in\Bbb{Z} \\[4pt]
0, &x=\frac12n, n\in\Bbb{Z} \\[4pt]
\frac1\pi \tan^{-1}(\cot(\pi x)), &\text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\end{align}$$
